00:05:08.000 --> 00:05:12.000
And then right underneath, you're going to see Cluster Kubernetes.

00:05:12.000 --> 00:05:16.000
Now, to tell you a little bit more about our demo environment here at Posit,

00:05:16.000 --> 00:05:19.000
it is all hosted in AWS, Amazon Web Services.

00:05:19.000 --> 00:05:24.000
And it's in a high-performance computing cluster, an HPC environment.

00:05:24.000 --> 00:05:27.000
And that environment is managed using something known as Kubernetes.

00:05:27.000 --> 00:05:29.000
Some of you may have heard of Kubernetes.

00:05:29.000 --> 00:05:33.000
That's one of these HPC managers that we support.

00:05:33.000 --> 00:05:36.000
If you also use Slurm, we can support that as well.

00:05:36.000 --> 00:05:38.000
Or you can also just run these tools on a single server.

00:05:38.000 --> 00:05:40.000
That's totally fine as well.

00:05:40.000 --> 00:05:44.000
But one of the advantages of using Kubernetes or Slurm

00:05:44.000 --> 00:05:49.000
is you can actually control this job's CPU and memory allocations.

00:05:49.000 --> 00:05:51.000
So if you just have like a small job,

00:05:51.000 --> 00:05:54.000
you want to maybe create a plot or a simple application,

00:05:55.000 --> 00:05:57.000
you can keep the CPU low, keep the memory low.

00:05:57.000 --> 00:06:01.000
And that's just great for managing compute resources.

00:06:01.000 --> 00:06:04.000
But if you have a higher compute or more demanding job,

00:06:04.000 --> 00:06:06.000
I can bump that up, for example.

00:06:06.000 --> 00:06:08.000
I can change the memory as well.

00:06:08.000 --> 00:06:11.000
So really good at managing resources.

00:06:11.000 --> 00:06:13.000
Then you'll see this last box right here.

00:06:13.000 --> 00:06:15.000
